<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/217</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Contract for improvement Grand Canal in Kiangsu providing for loan of
                            $3,000,000 secured by canal tolls has been signed subject to the
                            approval of directors American International Corporation. Highly
                            desirable that ratification should not be delayed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>